        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add LiteLLM provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a disabled-by-default LiteLLM provider for personal and team budget usage\n- integrate settings, config/environment overrides, token accounts, provider registries, widgets, icon resources, CLI selection, and docs\n- use the configured virtual key for least-privilege self lookup: `GET /key/info`, then `GET /user/info?user_id=...`\n- select team usage only by the authenticated key's exact `team_id`\n\n## Security\n- CodexBar does not request or store a LiteLLM master/management key\n- the virtual key is sent only as a Bearer header to the configured LiteLLM base URL\n- `/key/info` omits the `key` query parameter, avoiding credential exposure in URLs\n\n## Live E2E proof\nValidated on June 15, 2026 with the packaged ad-hoc-signed `CodexBar.app/Contents/Helpers/CodexBarCLI` against a disposable current official `ghcr.io/berriai/litellm-database:main-latest` proxy backed by Postgres 16.\n\nThe test created a user with a `$50` budget, a team with a `$100` budget, explicit team membership, and a team-bound virtual key. It verified virtual-key access to both `/key/info` and `/user/info`, then ran CodexBar with a `/v1` base URL to exercise management-path normalization.\n\nRedacted CLI result:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"provider\": \"litellm\",\n  \"source\": \"api\",\n  \"accountEmail\": \"litellm-e2e@example.com\",\n  \"personal\": \"$0.00 / $50.00\",\n  \"team\": \"Team codexbar-e2e-team: $0.00 / $100.00\",\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n\nAll disposable containers and networking were removed after the run.\n\n## Verification\n- focused LiteLLM/config/environment/registry suite: 59 tests passed\n- `make check`: SwiftFormat clean; SwiftLint 0 violations\n- `make test`: 39/39 shards passed\n- complete branch autoreview: no accepted/actionable findings\n- packaged CLI live E2E: personal and exact-team budget paths passed\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Risk\n- LiteLLM remains disabled by default and requires an explicit virtual key and HTTPS proxy URL in normal configuration\n- behavior depends on LiteLLM's current authenticated self-info endpoints; failures surface as provider API errors without falling back to privileged credentials",
